#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:149
msgid ""
"The number of sockets is deduced from the number of CPUs and the number of "
"cores. ``-smp 2,cores=1`` will define a machine with 2 sockets of 1 core, "
"whereas ``-smp 2,cores=2`` will define a machine with 1 socket of 2 cores. "
"``-smp 8,cores=2``, 4 sockets of 2 cores."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:155
msgid "BMC configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:157
msgid ""
"OpenPOWER systems negotiate the shutdown and reboot with their BMC. The QEMU "
"PowerNV machine embeds an IPMI BMC simulator using the iBT interface and "
"should offer the same power features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:161
msgid ""
"If you want to define your own BMC, use ``-nodefaults`` and specify one on "
"the command line :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:164
msgid "-device ipmi-bmc-sim,id=bmc0 -device isa-ipmi-bt,bmc=bmc0,irq=10"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:168
msgid ""
"The files `palmetto-SDR.bin <http://www.kaod.org/qemu/powernv/palmetto-SDR."
"bin>`__ and `palmetto-FRU.bin <http://www.kaod.org/qemu/powernv/palmetto-FRU."
"bin>`__ define a Sensor Data Record repository and a Field Replaceable Unit "
"inventory for a Palmetto BMC. They can be used to extend the QEMU BMC "
"simulator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:174
msgid ""
"-device ipmi-bmc-sim,sdrfile=./palmetto-SDR.bin,fruareasize=256,"
"frudatafile=./palmetto-FRU.bin,id=bmc0 \\\n"
"-device isa-ipmi-bt,bmc=bmc0,irq=10"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:179
msgid ""
"The PowerNV machine can also be run with an external IPMI BMC device "
"connected to a remote QEMU machine acting as BMC, using these options :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:183
msgid ""
"-chardev socket,id=ipmi0,host=localhost,port=9002,reconnect-ms=10000 \\\n"
"-device ipmi-bmc-extern,id=bmc0,chardev=ipmi0 \\\n"
"-device isa-ipmi-bt,bmc=bmc0,irq=10 \\\n"
"-nodefaults"
msgstr ""

