#: ../../../system/ppc/powernv.rst:199
msgid ""
"If no mtd drive is provided, the powernv platform will create a default PNOR "
"device using a tiny formatted PNOR in pc-bios/pnv-pnor.bin opened read-only "
"(PNOR changes will be persistent across reboots but not across invocations "
"of QEMU). If no defaults are used, an erased 128MB PNOR is provided (which "
"skiboot will probably not recognize since it is not formatted)."
